<FONT FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Geneva, Arial, sans
serif">
<P>To take into account 3e surprise rules, a psionicist caught flat-footed (meaning 
has not yet acted in the first round of a combat) can only have Mind Blank up 
as a defense, since it costs 0 PSPs and is assumed to be constantly maintained 
at all times. When a psioncist has a chance to act, he can choose which of his 
available Defense Modes to use for the next round. The choice remains until 
his turn to act comes in the next round.</P>
<P>Psionicists can still make 2 attacks in a single round with each use of an 
Attack Mode and unlimited defenses with each use of a Defense Mode.</P>
<P>
